1:32 PM Defendant Tyrel Orrin Wilberg appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Michael Hoffman appears via video appearance on behalf of the defendant. Acknowledges receipt of the complaint and waives reading, enters pleas of not guilty on misdemeanor counts. State asks for $1,000 cash bail with conditions of no use or possession of controlled substances. State recites prior criminal history and notes that defendant has other open cases with cash bail. He has also been revoked off of probation. Attorney Hoffman notes that the defendant is currently on a hold but is lifelong resident of the area. Court orders $1,000 cash bail with conditions of no use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 1, 2022 at 10:45 am.
